-- 
Obama Plans Alabama Trip to View Storm Damage, Recovery Effort

-- B y   R o g e r   R u n n i n g e n
-- 
2011-04-28T17:02:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-28/obama-plans-alabama-trip-to-view-storm-damage-recovery-effort.html
President  Barack Obama  will travel
to Alabama tomorrow to view tornado damage after storms
throughout much of the U.S. Southeast killed hundreds of people.  The White House announced that the president would meet
with Governor Robert Bentley, state and local officials and
families.  At least 200 people died in six states, with Alabama
hardest-hit, the Associated Press reported.  The president added Alabama to stops tomorrow in Florida
that include  Cape Canaveral  for the launch of the space shuttle,
and Miami, where he is scheduled to speak at a college
commencement.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Roger Runningen in Washington at 
 rrunningen@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Mark Silva at 
 msilva34@bloomberg.net  